<subSubSection lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1436,1970,2031]" lastBlockId="37.[151,1436,151,357]" lastPageId="37" lastPageNumber="38" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1970,1995]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the largest of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1905" box="[560,683,1972,1995]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[560,683,1972,1995]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Majeorona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species known to 
<collectingRegion box="[896,985,1971,1994]" country="Panama" name="Panama" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<collectingCountry box="[896,985,1971,1994]" name="Panama" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Panama</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
with body lengths of about 
<quantity box="[1307,1388,1971,1995]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.8" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="48.0">48 mm</quantity>
and wing spans of more than 
<quantity box="[469,572,2007,2031]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="120.0">120 mm</quantity>
. The basic brown and piceous coloration, the anterior extension of the postclypeus when viewed from the dorsal side and the fore wings have infuscation on the radial and radiomedial crossveins which easily distinguish it from 
<taxonomicName authority="Goding, 1925" authorityName="Goding" authorityYear="1925" box="[636,932,188,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Majeorona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncata">
<emphasis box="[636,768,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">M. truncata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[775,932,188,213]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refId="ref60803" refString="Goding, F. W. (1925) Synopsis of the Cicadidae of Ecuador. Revista del Colegio Nacional Rocafuerte, 7, 1 - 34." type="journal article">Goding, 1925</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1436,151,357]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,223,248]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Distribution.</emphasis>
The species is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[673,744,223,248]" name="Brazil" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[756,869,223,248]" name="Colombia" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[881,976,223,248]" name="Ecuador" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[988,1158,223,248]" country="France" name="Guyane" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<collectingCountry box="[988,1158,223,248]" name="French Guiana" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1169,1287,223,248]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1347,1436,224,247]" country="Panama" name="Panama" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<collectingCountry box="[1347,1436,224,247]" name="Panama" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Panama</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation box="[158,325,260,285]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refId="ref62259" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 a) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 1. Cicadidae. Section I. Tibiceninae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1502, i - vii + 1 - 585." type="journal article">Metcalf 1963a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[337,508,260,285]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refId="ref63407" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2011 a) Checklist of the cicadas of French Guiana including new records and the description of nine new species (Insecta, Hemiptera, Cicadoidea, Cicadidae). Zoosystema, 33, 377 - 418. https: // doi. org / 10.5252 / z 2011 n 3 a 6" type="journal article">Sanborn 2011a</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation box="[518,577,260,284]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refId="ref63516" refString="Sanborn, A. F. (2013) Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Hemiptera: Cicadoidea). With contributions to the bibliography by Martin H. Villet. Elsevier / Academic Press, San Diego, 1001 pp." type="book">2013</bibRefCitation>
; Maes 
<emphasis box="[656,712,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">et al.</emphasis>
2012; Sanborn &amp; Maes 2012). It was reported as being collected in 
<collectingRegion box="[180,303,295,320]" country="Panama" name="Panama" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<collectingCountry box="[180,269,296,319]" name="Panama" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Panama</collectingCountry>
by
</collectingRegion>
<bibRefCitation box="[310,578,295,320]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" refId="ref65723" refString="Wolda, H. &amp; Ramos, J. A. (1992) Cicadas in Panama, their distribution, seasonality and diversity. In: Quintero, D. &amp; Aiello, A. (Eds.), The insects of Panama and Mesoamerica. Selected studies. Oxford University Press, New York, pp. 271 - 279." type="book chapter">Wolda &amp; Ramos (1992)</bibRefCitation>
but without locality data.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
